parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front brake lever becomes frozen or stuck
the rear brake pedal becomes stiff or hard to press
the brakes fail to engage
or the ABS warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly maintain the brake fluid can lead to ABS module failure, which can cause brake malfunctions, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid contamination
corrosion
or degradation
which can cause the ABS module to fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a warning or notification of an impending ABS module failure can lead to sudden brake malfunctions, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: No warning lights or notifications prior to ABS module failure
sudden brake failure without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TBW system can cause the throttle to malfunction, leading to loss of speed control, stalling, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The throttle goes into idle mode
the bike shuts down
loss of throttle response
surging or bucking
engine cuts in and out
and sudden loss of speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of braking control, increased risk of accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The front brake lever becomes frozen
unable to apply the brake
and failure of the ABS module.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including engine stalling, loss of speed control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud cracking noise when attempting to start the vehicle
starter clutch causes starter gear to disengage
and intermittent failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of running lights can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: No running lights in the front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control can cause unexpected engine revving, sudden loss of power, and the vehicle to go into "limp mode," which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine suddenly revs without engaging the throttle
the engine RPMs increase to their maximum
the check engine light comes on
the engine drops to idle speed
the engine fails to respond to throttle control
the vehicle goes into "limp mode."

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause a loss of power, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stalls and quits
the check engine light comes on
the engine RPMs drop to idle speed
the engine fails to respond to throttle control
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose or Missing Engine Mount Bolts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or missing engine mount bolts can cause the engine to vibrate excessively, leading to premature wear on engine components, and potentially causing the engine to stall or lose power.
symptoms: Unusual noise from the undercarriage
warning lights on the dashboard
battery light illumination
loose or missing engine mount bolts.
